    <title>Manage section forms</title>
    <section>
        <title>Create a section form</title>
        <para>Section forms are separated automatically by data element category combinations, which
            produce a spreadsheet like data entry form for each section.</para>
        <orderedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>Open the <emphasis role="bold">Maintenance</emphasis> app and click <emphasis
                        role="bold">Data set</emphasis> > <emphasis role="bold">Data
                    set</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>In the list, find the data set you want to create a section form for.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click the options menu and select <emphasis role="bold">Manage
                        sections</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click the add button.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>In the <emphasis role="bold">Name</emphasis> field, type the name of the
                    section.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>In the <emphasis role="bold">Description</emphasis> field, type a description
                    of the section.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Select a <emphasis role="bold">Category
                        <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160629T150155+0200" comment="For SMe: Only default to choose... What does default mean?
- Depends on the cat combo, not always default." flag="done"?>combination<?oxy_comment_end?></emphasis>.</para>
                <para>
                    <note>
                        <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160629T150351+0200" comment="For SME: Still correct?
 - Yes, for now. " flag="done"?>
                        <para>You can only use one category combination per section.</para>
                        <?oxy_comment_end?>
                    </note>
                </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Select data elements and assign them.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>(Optional) Sort the data elements within the section by using the up and down
                    arrows to the left of the assigned data elements field.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Save</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Repeat
                    <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160630T172809+0200" comment="At next release: Add x-refs to the steps to claify." flag="done"?>add<?oxy_comment_end?>
                    section steps for each section you want to have in your section form.</para>
                <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160630T173012+0200" comment="At next release: Rewrite para." flag="done"?>
                <para>In the <emphasis role="bold">Data entry</emphasis> app you can now use the
                    section form. The section form appears automatically when sections are available
                    for the selected data set. Data sets which have section forms will automatically
                    display the section form.</para>
                <?oxy_comment_end?>
            </listitem>
        </orderedlist>
        <example>
            <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160629T121605+0200" comment="Before release: replace screenshot"?>
            <title>Section form example</title>
            <?oxy_comment_end?>
            <para>Note
                h<?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160630T174604+0200" comment="For SME: Is example correct?"?>ow
                each data element category has been separated into a separate section, and a data
                entry table has been automatically generated by the system<?oxy_comment_end?>. Use
                of section forms in combination with data element categories can drastically reduce
                the amount of time which is required to create data entry forms for data
                sets.</para>
            <screenshot>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata width="80%" align="center"
                            fileref="resources/images/dhis2UserManual/section_form.png" format="PNG"
                        />
                    </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </screenshot>
        </example>
    </section>
